comments.text:
+Shan Burrick  I think she was just referring to the fact that they are 
hard shell tacos. For the most part Mexican people generally only make soft 
tacos with corn tortillas. My mom makes hard shell tacos but refers to them 
as being like taco bell tacos. There are hard shell taquitios/flautas but 
they are rolled tacos which are usually fried once they are rolled with the 
meat inside. Hard shell tacos are more like the american version of tacos. 
Kind of like how Panda Express is the Americanized version on of Chinese 
food it's similar but not authentic.
